00:14:07.112 --> 00:14:08.881
that have been breached.

00:14:08.881 --> 00:14:11.050
So I wouldn't say it's
impossible for someone

00:14:11.050 --> 00:14:13.786
to breach the bank but
I will say that banks

00:14:13.786 --> 00:14:17.656
and financial institutions as
a whole do a much better job

00:14:17.656 --> 00:14:19.758 align:start size:97% position:3%
than the federal government,
the state government,

00:14:19.758 --> 00:14:21.794
the county government,
the city government does

00:14:21.794 --> 00:14:25.397
in protecting people's
assets and information.

00:14:25.397 --> 00:14:27.566
You take a bank like
City National Bank

00:14:27.566 --> 00:14:29.201
or Chase in Manhattan,

00:14:29.201 --> 00:14:32.471 align:start size:84% position:16%
they spend about a
half a billion dollars
a year, every year

00:14:32.471 --> 00:14:34.940
on technology to
keep criminals out.

00:14:34.940 --> 00:14:37.776
They're constantly staying one
step ahead of the criminals,

00:14:37.776 --> 00:14:39.745 align:start size:88% position:13%
understand what they're
doing and they have

00:14:39.745 --> 00:14:43.315
a lot of fail safe programs
in place to protect them.

00:14:43.315 --> 00:14:46.685 align:start size:97% position:3%
We don't have that, we have
an infrastructure today

00:14:46.685 --> 00:14:50.556 align:start position:0%
with electrical grid that
hasn't been updated in 25 years.

00:14:50.556 --> 00:14:53.859 align:start size:88% position:13%
There's a lot of weak
spots in our government.

00:14:53.859 --> 00:14:55.828
Our Medicare and
Medicaid last year

00:14:55.828 --> 00:15:00.199
