00:46:48.005 --> 00:46:53.010
mentioned that I had trained
two generations of FBI agents

00:46:54.444 --> 00:46:56.914 align:start size:97% position:3%
during my career and that's
been a wonderful thing for me.

00:46:56.914 --> 00:47:00.250
- The FBI has had some
problems in its past,

00:47:00.250 --> 00:47:02.653
it was a bit problematic
around the Hoover years.

00:47:02.653 --> 00:47:06.256 align:start size:88% position:13%
And now there is concern
about whether or not

00:47:06.256 --> 00:47:10.627 align:start size:94% position:6%
the FBI is following
certain ethical guidelines

00:47:10.627 --> 00:47:12.629
in its dealings.

00:47:12.629 --> 00:47:14.932
How does that concern you?

00:47:14.932 --> 00:47:18.435 line:0%
- Well, like in every
in every organization

00:47:18.435 --> 00:47:20.037 line:0%
there are a few bad people.

00:47:20.037 --> 00:47:24.741 align:start position:0%
I truly believe that you
cannot be involved politically,

00:47:24.741 --> 00:47:26.243
you can have your
political thoughts,

00:47:26.243 --> 00:47:28.712 align:start size:88% position:13%
you cannot let them
interfere in your work.

00:47:28.712 --> 00:47:32.049
The 13,000 agents
that are out there,

00:47:32.049 --> 00:47:34.985
they don't let politics
interfere in their work.

00:47:34.985 --> 00:47:36.887
I think this was a
handful of people,

00:47:36.887 --> 00:47:40.290
who obviously now have
been fired and dismissed,

00:47:40.290 --> 00:47:43.627 align:start size:84% position:16%
but who let politics
get involved with
their decision-making

00:47:43.627 --> 00:47:45.729
and that was wrong.

00:47:45.729 --> 00:47:47.231
And you can't become political.

00:47:47.231 --> 00:47:49.199
And obviously you have to serve

00:47:49.199 --> 00:47:52.569
whatever president the
public puts in place.

00:47:52.569 --> 00:47:54.438
They're your president, you
have to serve the president,

00:47:54.438 --> 00:47:55.873 align:start size:84% position:16%
whether you like
them, don't like them,

00:47:55.873 --> 00:47:58.308
don't believe in their politics.

00:47:58.308 --> 00:48:01.478
That's not your decision
to make as an FBI agent.

00:48:01.478 --> 00:48:04.081 align:start position:0%
And when you investigate a
crime you investigate the crime

00:48:04.081 --> 00:48:07.517 align:start size:94% position:6%
based on facts and
information you've gotten.

00:48:07.517 --> 00:48:12.022 align:start size:97% position:3%
And as for the FBI and
their over 100 year history,

00:48:12.022 --> 00:48:15.192 align:start size:97% position:3%
their sole job, as they
remind people all the time,

00:48:15.192 --> 00:48:17.594
is only an investigative arm

00:48:17.594 --> 00:48:19.963
of the Department of Justice.

00:48:19.963 --> 00:48:21.732
So they investigate the crime,

00:48:21.732 --> 00:48:24.902 align:start size:88% position:13%
they bring the evidence
to the US attorney,

00:48:24.902 --> 00:48:26.103
or in this case the
Attorney General,

00:48:26.103 --> 00:48:27.971
say here's all the evidence.

00:48:27.971 --> 00:48:30.374 align:start size:88% position:13%
And the Attorney General
or the US Attorney

00:48:30.374 --> 00:48:33.610
makes a decision whether to
prosecute or not prosecute.

00:48:34.578 --> 00:48:36.046
So in my personal opinion,

00:48:36.046 --> 00:48:39.283 align:start position:0%
Director Comey should have never
ever made those statements.

00:48:39.283 --> 00:48:41.818
It was not his place to
make those statements.

00:48:41.818 --> 00:48:44.154
He should have simply said
to the Attorney General,

00:48:44.154 --> 00:48:46.523
I'm not doing that,
that's not my job.

00:48:46.523 --> 00:48:48.859 align:start size:84% position:16%
And if you force me
to do it, I'll resign,

00:48:48.859 --> 00:48:52.262
and that will look even worse
if I tell people why I resign.

00:48:52.262 --> 00:48:55.732
I think that was where it
all started, the mistake.

00:48:55.732 --> 00:48:57.467
He should have never done that.

00:48:57.467 --> 00:49:00.170 align:start size:84% position:16%
I think he was a
little more political.

00:49:00.170 --> 00:49:02.272 align:start size:88% position:13%
I not only knew Director
Muller very well

00:49:02.272 --> 00:49:04.107
