So you got a catalog
yesterday from Macy's,

00:50:07.738 --> 00:50:09.706 align:start size:88% position:13%
you looked at it, wasn't
anything you wanted,

00:50:09.706 --> 00:50:11.508
so you threw it away.

00:50:11.508 --> 00:50:12.709 align:start size:84% position:16%
But on the back
cover of the catalog

00:50:12.709 --> 00:50:14.911 align:start size:84% position:16%
was your name and
address, your barcode,

00:50:14.911 --> 00:50:17.948
source code, ID number.

00:50:17.948 --> 00:50:19.616
That's all I need to become you.

00:50:19.616 --> 00:50:21.084
So you want to shred that.

00:50:21.084 --> 00:50:23.020 align:start size:97% position:3%
You went to the grocery
store and you wrote a check.

00:50:23.020 --> 00:50:25.055 align:start size:84% position:16%
On the check was your
name and address,

00:50:25.055 --> 00:50:27.424 align:start size:84% position:16%
phone number, bank's
name and address,

00:50:27.424 --> 00:50:29.159
account number at your bank,

00:50:29.159 --> 00:50:31.194 align:start size:81% position:19%
routing number
into your account,

00:50:31.194 --> 00:50:32.996
that you're wiring instructions.

00:50:32.996 --> 00:50:36.433 align:start size:94% position:6%
Signature on the signature
card at your bank.

00:50:36.433 --> 00:50:37.634
Then the clerk wrote down

00:50:37.634 --> 00:50:39.936 align:start size:88% position:13%
your North Dakota
driver's license number

00:50:39.936 --> 00:50:41.638
and your date of
birth on the front.

00:50:41.638 --> 00:50:43.173
You don't get the check back.

00:50:43.173 --> 00:50:46.410
We live in truncation so you
get an image of the check.

00:50:46.410 --> 00:50:49.479 align:start position:0%
The check goes to that company's
headquarters in Chicago

00:50:49.479 --> 00:50:52.015
where it sits in a
warehouse for 65 days

00:50:52.015 --> 00:50:54.051 align:start size:84% position:16%
and then they
physically destroy it.

00:50:54.051 --> 00:50:56.153
Anyone who would see
the face of that check

00:50:57.320 --> 00:50:58.288 align:start size:81% position:19%
could draft on
your bank account,

00:50:58.288 --> 00:50:59.823
wire money out of your account.

00:50:59.823 --> 00:51:02.459
So I don't get over paranoid,
I'm a little old-fashioned,

00:51:02.459 --> 00:51:03.393
I write a check to
pay the mortgage

00:51:03.393 --> 00:51:05.128
or write a check to pay a loan,

00:51:05.128 --> 00:51:06.329 align:start size:94% position:6%
but I'm very careful about
where I write a check.

00:51:06.329 --> 00:51:07.998 align:start size:84% position:16%
Because I'm actually
handing someone

00:51:07.998 --> 00:51:10.700
information with all
my banking information

00:51:10.700 --> 00:51:12.702
on a piece of paper.

00:51:13.570 --> 00:51:15.272
I don't own a debit card.

00:51:15.272 --> 00:51:16.473
I've never owned one,

00:51:16.473 --> 00:51:19.142 align:start size:84% position:16%
never allowed my three
sons to have one.

00:51:19.142 --> 00:51:22.679
A long time ago while writing
a book on financial security,

00:51:22.679 --> 00:51:27.584 align:start position:0%
I asked myself how would someone
remove 99.9% of their risk.

00:51:27.584 --> 00:51:30.687
And the answer was to use
the safest form of payment

00:51:30.687 --> 00:51:32.656
that exists on the
face of the earth.

00:51:32.656 --> 00:51:35.092
And that is a credit card.

00:51:35.092 --> 00:51:37.127
Credit card, Visa, MasterCard,

00:51:37.127 --> 00:51:39.129
American Express, Discover card.

00:51:39.129 --> 00:51:42.332
Not a debit-credit
but a credit card.

00:51:42.332 --> 00:51:43.934
And every day of my life

00:51:43.934 --> 00:51:46.103
I spend the credit
card company's money.

00:51:46.103 --> 00:51:47.604
I never spend my money,

00:51:47.604 --> 00:51:50.173 align:start position:0%
my money sits in a money market
account, it earns interest.

00:51:50.173 --> 00:51:53.310 align:start position:0%
No one knows where it is because
it's not exposed to anyone.

00:51:53.310 --> 00:51:56.546 align:start size:88% position:13%
I only expose the credit
card company's money.

00:51:56.546 --> 00:51:58.949
I will do everything I
can to protect the card,

00:51:58.949 --> 00:52:00.584
but if someone gets my number

00:52:00.584 --> 00:52:03.687 align:start size:84% position:16%
and they charge a
million dollars on my
credit card tomorrow

00:52:03.687 --> 00:52:07.591
by federal law my liability
is zero, I have no liability.

00:52:07.591 --> 00:52:10.193
If I buy something online
and use my credit card

00:52:10.193 --> 00:52:12.195 align:start size:84% position:16%
and they don't deliver
it I'm covered.

00:52:12.195 --> 00:52:14.297 align:start size:94% position:6%
If I buy something
online and it comes broke

00:52:14.297 --> 00:52:16.633
and they refuse to take
it back, I'm covered.

00:52:16.633 --> 00:52:19.402
If I buy something online
from a fictitious website

00:52:19.402 --> 00:52:21.238 align:start size:81% position:19%
because I don't
know is fictitious

00:52:21.238 --> 00:52:23.473
and I never get it, I'm covered.

00:52:23.473 --> 00:52:26.510
Every time I pay my bill or
part of my bill every month,

00:52:26.510 --> 00:52:28.712
my credit score goes up,

00:52:28.712 --> 00:52:30.914 align:start size:94% position:6%
so I keep building credit
on my credit score.

00:52:30.914 --> 00:52:33.383
When you use a debit card
every time you reach for it

00:52:33.383 --> 00:52:35.652 align:start size:94% position:6%
you're exposing the money
in your bank account.

00:52:35.652 --> 00:52:38.288 align:start size:94% position:6%
The only money they gonna
steel is your money.

00:52:38.288 --> 00:52:41.825 align:start position:0%
So in every post-investigation,
Target, Home Depot,

00:52:41.825 --> 00:52:44.728 align:start size:97% position:3%
every one of those came
down to the simple question,

00:52:44.728 --> 00:52:45.929
what happened?

00:52:45.929 --> 00:52:47.731 align:start size:81% position:19%
Well, I had a Visa
card at Target

00:52:47.731 --> 00:52:49.533
so they just canceled my card,

00:52:49.533 --> 00:52:52.669 align:start size:97% position:3%
I think two days later FedEx
delivered me a new card.

00:52:52.669 --> 00:52:54.404
That was the last
I heard about it.

00:52:54.404 --> 00:52:57.440 align:start size:94% position:6%
Oh no, I had a debit
card, and they took $3,000

00:52:57.440 --> 00:52:58.942
out of my checking account,

00:52:58.942 --> 00:53:01.411
and it took me two months
to get the $3,000 back

00:53:01.411 --> 00:53:04.748
while the bank said they
were investigating it.

00:53:04.748 --> 00:53:08.752
You do nothing for your
credit score whatsoever.

00:53:08.752 --> 00:53:12.122 align:start position:0%
If you could use that debit
card 20 times a day for 20 years

00:53:12.122 --> 00:53:13.323
your credit will
not move this much.

00:53:13.323 --> 00:53:16.593 align:start size:88% position:13%
So I had three sons that
went off to college.

00:53:16.593 --> 00:53:19.563
I said to them I'm not
giving you a debit card.

00:53:19.563 --> 00:53:22.666
I've actually applied for
a credit card in your name.

00:53:22.666 --> 00:53:24.401
So it's your card.

00:53:24.401 --> 00:53:26.269
Of course you're 18
you have no credit.

00:53:26.269 --> 00:53:27.904
So I had to guarantee the card.

00:53:29.105 --> 00:53:30.574
And that means three
things will happen.

00:53:30.574 --> 00:53:32.842
One, the bill comes to me,
I'm responsible for the bill.

00:53:32.842 --> 00:53:34.511
So if you're spending a
lot of time in the bar

00:53:34.511 --> 00:53:36.046
I'm gonna know it.

00:53:36.046 --> 00:53:40.684
Two, every time I pay the bill
it's gonna go on your credit.

00:53:40.684 --> 00:53:42.886
So five years from now,
four years from now,

00:53:42.886 --> 00:53:44.321
when you graduated from college

00:53:44.321 --> 00:53:46.489 align:start size:88% position:13%
you should have a credit
score of about 800.

00:53:46.489 --> 00:53:48.325
You want to buy a
car, buy a house,

00:53:48.325 --> 00:53:50.327
you can do that without
me you don't need me

00:53:50.327 --> 00:53:52.162
to do that for you.

00:53:52.162 --> 00:53:53.930
And of course I control
the limit on the card,

00:53:53.930 --> 00:53:56.233 align:start size:94% position:6%
so whatever I think you
need to spend every month,

00:53:56.233 --> 00:53:58.235 align:start size:81% position:19%
that'll be the
limit of the card.

00:53:58.235 --> 00:53:59.803
One of the best things you
can do for your children

00:53:59.803 --> 00:54:03.340 line:0%
is to teach them early on to
build credit in their name.

00:54:03.340 --> 00:54:06.076 line:0%
We have a lot of young people
now only use a debit card.

00:54:06.076 --> 00:54:08.878
They graduate from college,
they come back to Fargo,

00:54:08.878 --> 00:54:10.580
they get a beautiful job.

00:54:10.580 --> 00:54:13.483
They go down to rent
an apartment, they
fill out the lease,

00:54:13.483 --> 00:54:15.518 align:start size:88% position:13%
and the manager says
son, you have no credit.

00:54:15.518 --> 00:54:17.854
You don't even have a credit
file with the credit bureau.

00:54:17.854 --> 00:54:21.391
So you're gonna have to have
your parents co-sign the lease.

00:54:21.391 --> 00:54:23.426
So one of the best
things you can do

00:54:23.426 --> 00:54:24.894
is teach them to build credit.

00:54:24.894 --> 00:54:26.763
You know 30 years ago credit
was all about do I get the car,

00:54:26.763 --> 00:54:27.998
do I get the home.

00:54:27.998 --> 00:54:30.400 align:start size:84% position:16%
Everything today,
everything literally

00:54:30.400 --> 00:54:31.901
is based on your credit.

00:54:31.901 --> 00:54:34.237 align:start size:94% position:6%
So if you apply for a job,
they check your credit.

00:54:34.237 --> 00:54:36.506 align:start size:97% position:3%
You apply for auto insurance,
they check your credit.

00:54:36.506 --> 00:54:38.775
Life insurance, they
check your credit.

00:54:38.775 --> 00:54:40.644 align:start size:84% position:16%
Health insurance, they
check your credit.

00:54:40.644 --> 00:54:42.479
No matter what it is,
open a bank account,

00:54:42.479 --> 00:54:43.647
they check your credit.

00:54:43.647 --> 00:54:46.082 align:start size:84% position:16%
So everything is
based on your credit,

00:54:46.082 --> 00:54:48.618
and it's very important
to teach young people

00:54:48.618 --> 00:54:50.787
to build credit and
use that credit.

00:54:50.787 --> 00:54:53.223
And then finally I would
say freeze your credit.

00:54:53.223 --> 00:54:55.025
And if you don't want
to freeze your credit

00:54:55.025 --> 00:54:56.760
then use a credit
monitoring service,

00:54:56.760 --> 00:54:58.728
they're are like
$13, $15 a month,

00:54:58.728 --> 00:55:01.131
companies like Life
Lock, Privacy Guard,

00:55:01.131 --> 00:55:03.066
where they monitor
your credit for you

00:55:03.066 --> 00:55:04.601
and notify you in real time

00:55:04.601 --> 00:55:06.469 align:start size:88% position:13%
if someone's attempting
to use your name,

00:55:06.469 --> 00:55:08.038 align:start size:84% position:16%
social security
number, date of birth,

00:55:08.038 --> 00:55:09.973 align:start size:84% position:16%
or some of that
personal information

00:55:09.973 --> 00:55:12.042 align:start size:84% position:16%
so you can do
something about it.

00:55:12.042 --> 00:55:15.412
You have to be proactive,
you can't be reactive.

00:55:15.412 --> 00:55:17.781
This is not 30 years ago,

00:55:17.781 --> 00:55:19.683 align:start size:88% position:13%
you have to be a
smarter consumer today.

00:55:19.683 --> 00:55:21.551
You certainly have to be a
smarter businessman today.

00:55:21.551 --> 00:55:23.219
So you cannot rely
on the government,

00:55:23.219 --> 00:55:24.521
you cannot rely on the bank,

00:55:24.521 --> 00:55:26.856
you cannot rely on the
police to protect you.

00:55:26.856 --> 00:55:29.326
You have to learn
to protect yourself

00:55:29.326 --> 00:55:31.461
and take the steps
necessary to do that.

